description: Drawing inspiration from the underground rave scene of St. Petersburg is the Nike women's Air Force 1 Fontanka 'Pearl White University Red.' The low-top's reconstructed look features a cream-colored leather upper with offset stitching doubled-up tongues and a multi-layered pieced-together eyestay. A similar aesthetic is continued on the synthetic suede Swoosh and heel tab with black zigzag stitching. On the bottom is a tonal midsole with a red 'cassette tape' of Nike React foam embedded in the heel.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid Pink Shadow
description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid 'Pink Shadow' gives a new take of the iconic sneaker design renewed in Black and Hot Punch. Its upper accentuates a leather base with overlays and the trademark Wings’ Logo. On the upper a Swoosh emphasizes the design with a nylon woven tongue. The midsole is built on top of a rubber outsole with a circular build for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid Sisterhood (W)
description: The Wmns Air Jordan 1 Mid 'Sisterhood' is a stylized take on the classic basketball shoe. Built entirely with leather the upper appears in a mix of black white and Game Royal with faux stitching comprised of heavy woven cords on the quarter panel and heel. Underfoot the midsole houses Air for cushioning giving way to a concentric rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High 85 Varsity Red
description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High '85 'Varsity Red' emerges with a look that essentially flips the iconic 'Banned' colorway. Built with leather the upper sports a black base overlaid by Varsity Red. A padded nylon tongue supports the fit while underfoot a white Air midsole provides cushioning and contrast.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 SE Love for All (W)
description: Releasing to celebrate the romantic holiday the Wmns Air Force 1 '07 SE 'Love For All' emerges with a colorway fit for the occasion. Built with a white leather base the translucent Swoosh branding on the side wall appears in pink reading 'Love' on the lateral side and 'Love for All' on the medial. The tongue tag and heel patch add further pink to the look while the custom sockliner includes playful care instructions like 'Handle with Respect' and 'My Love Runs Hot.'

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High UNC Patent (W)
description: The Wmns Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Blue Chill' released ahead of the 2019 NBA All-Star Game held in Charlotte North Carolina. As a result the shoe's patent leather upper in Blue Chill white and black sports a University of North Carolina feel with Obsidian on the tongue and laces. A white Air midsole provides cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low Silver Snake (2021)
description: Originally released in 2001 as one of three CO.JP Air Force 1 'B' styles the Air Force 1 '3M Snake' 2021 released in February 2021. The shoe's upper is built with a black leather base overlaid by matte silver and accented by faux snakeskin detailing on the Swoosh branding. The usual perforations on the toe box provide breathability while underfoot the midsole houses Air for cushioning giving way to a concentric rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low G-Dragon Peaceminusone Para-Noise
description: The G-Dragon x Air Force 1 '07 'Para-noise' showcases the K-pop star’s unique take on the venerable Nike silhouette. The black coating on the sneaker’s leather upper is designed to wear away with time revealing a colorful design created by G-Dragon himself. Additional personal touches include an embroidered daisy on the tongue and black brush-stroke effects on the white midsole.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High Game Royal
description: Placing a new palette on a classic silhouette the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Game Royal' keeps the iconic color-blocked aesthetic of the ‘Chicago’ variant but swaps red for Game Royal blue. The sneaker keeps its Summit White side panel and toe box along with its black Swoosh and Wings logo.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High Trophy Room Chicago
description: The Trophy Room x Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG SP 'Chicago' was limited to just 12000 pairs. Inspired by 'the freezeout' in which a rookie Michael Jordan was reportedly denied the ball by his veteran teammates at the 1985 NBA All-Star Game the shoe emerges with a frozen finish throughout its construction. Designed by Marcus Jordan's sneaker boutique the shoe's upper is built with leather finished in white black and Varsity Red with the lateral heel sporting Michael Jordan's signature. Underfoot an off-white Air midsole provides cushioning giving way to a translucent rubber outsole with a concentric pattern for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low Mulberry (W)
description: Treating the classic silhouette to a refreshed two-tone color scheme is the women's Air Jordan 1 Low SE 'Light Mulberry.' A vibrant violet hue is featured on the leather upper with contrasting black branding elements that include a tumbled leather Swoosh a stitched Wings logo on the heel overlay and an embroidered Jumpman on the nylon tongue. The low-top is built on a durable rubber cupsole with off-white sidewalls and a purple rubber outsole.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low CLOT Blue Silk
description: The CLOT x Air Force 1 PRM 'Royal Silk' dropped in 2019 marking the third AF1 collaboration between Nike and the Hong Kong streetwear brand. Reflecting the concept of yin and yang the sneaker’s embroidered Game Royal silk upper is meant to be worn away with wear revealing a hidden grey leather build underneath. A grippy gum rubber outsole anchors the unique design.

shoeName: Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves Rush Maroon (without Bracelet)
description: Remixing the vintage running shoe from 1987 with the Amsterdam retailer's take is the Patta x Nike Air max 1 'Rush Maroon.' The upper is made of silver mesh with contrasting maroon leather overlays including a wavy mudguard marked with an embroidered mini-Swoosh on the lateral side. Nike Air branding on the heel overlay features orange lettering which matches the sneaker's upper eyelets and textile collar lining. Patta's script logo is on the woven tongue tag with lightweight cushioning in the off-white polyurethane midsole with a visible Air unit nestled under the heel.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High Union Los Angeles Black Toe
description: The Union x Air Jordan 1 Retro High 'Black Toe' draws inspiration from the venerable Los Angeles retailer's love of thrifting and DIY culture creating a new take on the sneaker that started it all. In addition to a pre-yellowed midsole for a vintage look a mismatched collar is attached to the rest of the upper with zigzag stitching a creative nod to makeshift design.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low SNKRS Day (W)
description: Giving the nod to the fourth anniversary of the SNKRS app in Europe the Air Jordan 1 Low 'SNKRS Day' released on August 8 2021. Built with leather the shoe's upper appears in yellow overlaid by tan suede and supported by a mesh collar. The Swoosh and forefoot overlay are built with suede sporting a series of leopard spots to accent the design. The SNKRS anniversary date joins Jumpman branding on the tongue tag while underfoot more leopard sports appear through the translucent rubber outsole which offers traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low Kith Knicks Home
description: The Kith x Air Force 1 Low 'NYC Home' released as part of a collaboration with Kith. Inspired by the retailer's hometown team the shoe's classic basketball construction emerges with a white leather base highlighted by mismatched gradient TPU Swooshes in an New York Knicks mix of Rush Blue and Brilliant Orange. The heel patch includes Kith Air branding and the lateral heel includes a callout to New York City. Underfoot an Air midsole gives way to an icy blue translucent rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low PSG Paris Saint-Germain
description: A collaboration between Jordan Brand and Paris Saint-Germain the Paris Saint-Germain x Air Jordan 1 Low gives the nod to the renowned French soccer club. The shoe features inspiration from the team's alternate kit with a black nubuck upper complemented by tonal leather Swoosh branding. The heel sports a hybrid PSG/Jumpman logo with 'Paname' in Infrared on the quarter panel and inside the tongue to complete the look.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low Gold Toe
description: The Air Jordan 1 Low 'Gold Toe' brings an elevated colorway to the low-top iteration of Michael Jordan's first signature shoe. The upper is built with both leather and patent leather finished in a mix of black white and metallic gold with a contrasting 'Wings' logo on the heel. Underfoot the white midsole houses Air for cushioning giving way to a black rubber outsole with a concentric pattern for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 High FlyEase Light Smoke Grey
description: The Air Jordan 1 High FlyEase 'Light Smoke Grey' gives a new take of the legendary shoe design updated in Light Smoke Grey and Smoke Grey. Its upper spotlights a leather base with overlays and the trademark Jordan Wings’ Logo. On the upper a Swoosh emphasizes the design with a nylon contstructed tongue. The midsole is built on top of a rubber outsole with a circular build for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low Multicolor Snakeskin (2020) (W)
description: Also known as the 'Multi Snakeskin' the Wmns Air Jordan 1 Low 'Coachella' released in April 2020. Built with a black tumbled leather base the upper is highlighted by a series of colorful snakeksin overlays. Metallic gold detailing accents the side wall while underfoot a white midsole provides cushioning and contrast.

shoeName: Vans Slip-On Checkerboard
description: In the late 1970s Steve Van Doren son of Vans founder Paul Van Doren noticed that skateboarders in Southern California started to customize their Vans by coloring checkerboard style patterns on the shoes midsole. With this inspiration the Vans Slip On Checkerboard was created.The Vans Slip On Checkerboard is a cultural icon. First introduced to a global audience through an unforgettable cameo on Sean Penn's slacker character Jeff Spiccoli in the 1982 film Fast Times at Ridgemont High the checkered Vans Slip On is a monument in the Vans line and a street staple. It features a canvas black and white checkerboard patterned upper with a branded Vans tab. At the base a white and gum waffle cup sole with a red heel patch completes the design.This 2019 iteration of the Vans Slip On Checkerboard retailed for $65.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High Dior
description: Part of a collection between the fashion house and Jordan Brand the Dior x Air Jordan 1 High released in April 2020. The shoe's Italian leather upper appears in a mix of white and grey with a Dior Oblique jacquard Swoosh contrasting the side wall. The tongue tag and 'Wings' logo sport co-branding with further branding revealed by the icy translucent outsole.

shoeName: adidas Yung-1 Dragon Ball Z Frieza
description: The collaboration between adidas Originals and Dragon Ball Z memorializes three famous battles from the Japanese anime series by pitting two silhouettes against one another. In the Son Goku vs. Frieza duel a ZX 500 RM characterizes the show’s hero Goku while a Yung-1 represents DBZ’s primary antagonist Frieza. This homage to the '90s era reveres Frieza’s final form with purple grey and lilac overlays in both suede and leather and a corduroy medial panel adding supplementary color. A fully rendered Dragon Ball Z graphic covers the insole.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High Yellow Ochre
description: The Air Jordan 1 High OG 'Yellow Ochre' was released in Europe in May 2018 as part of the 'Best Hand in the Game' collection. The group consists of four Air Jordan 1 colorways each representing an important milestone in the career of Michael Jordan. All four shoes in the collection feature black toe blocking and a hand of cards on the right insole — the Yellow Ochre colorway celebrating Jordan's five MVP titles with a royal flush — a detailed perspective of the player's unparalleled competitive spirit.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High Off-White White
description: The OFF-WHITEx Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'White' inspired by Air Jordan 1 colorways is a reimagination of its 'Chicago' predecessor. Designed by Virgil Abloh the model features a premium all-white leather and mesh upper with deconstructed Swoosh branding and blue detail as well as Wings logos on the ankles. It is accentuated on the midsole with black "AIR" markings on the side panels with black ' Off-WhiteTM for NIKE ' text and orange tabs.

shoeName: Nike Air Max Penny 1 Game Royal
description: Debuting in 1995 this signature iteration of the Penny 1 features a combination of leather and synthetic upper with a Magic-style pinstripe detail on the tongue. The full-length Phylon midsole features Max Air in the heel and Zoom Air in the forefoot for cushioning while Hardaway’s ‘1 Cent’ logo appears on the heel.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low Racer Blue White
description: The Air Jordan 1 Low SE 'Racer Blue' gives a new iteration of the iconic shoe form redesigned in Racer Blue and Psychic Blue. Its upper accentuates a leather base with overlays and the trademark Wings’ Logo. On the upper a Swoosh emphasizes the design with a Nike branded nylon tongue. The midsole is built on top of a rubber outsole with a circular build for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid SE Sprite Blue (GS)
description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE GS 'Sprite' is a shoe offered exclusively in kid sizes and enlivens the classic silhouette with eye-catching elements. Multicolor laces secure an upper that combines a white leather base with a Racer Blue Swoosh and woven textile overlays in Dark Powder Blue. Neon green accents are featured on the Jumpman logo on the tongue tag Wings branding on the lateral collar flap and a pair of webbing pull tabs that make the shoe easy to get into. The mid-top is built on a standard AJ1 rubber cupsole with a foam wedge and an encapsulated Air-sole unit in the heel.

shoeName: Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT PSG Paris Saint-Germain
description: The Paris Saint-Germain x Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Comfort 'Paris' features a classic colorway with vibrant accents. The shoe's upper is built with suede finished in off-white and contrasted by black on the nubuck overlays. The die-cut Swoosh highlights the look with reflective iridescent detailing while the deconstructed collar and 'Wings' logo bring a gradient accent to the design. The heel includes Paris Saint-Germain branding and underfoot Zoom Air in the heel of the midsole provides cushioning.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High White Black Volt University Gold (GS)
description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG GS 'Volt Gold' is a grade-school shoe with vibrant accents. The shoe's upper is built with leather finished primarily in white and contrasted by black. The collar highlights the look in Volt while University Gold emerges on the heel. The collar as well as the tongue also incorporates exposed foam. Underfoot the midsole houses the usual Air for cushioning giving way to a concentric rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro Low White Ghost Green Black
description: Featuring a pastel look the Air Jordan 1 Low OG 'Ghost Green' released in May 2021. Built with a leather base the shoe's upper appears in white overlaid by synthetic suede in Ghost Green. The Swoosh branding on the side wall is matched by an embroidered mini-Swoosh at the lateral forefoot while the metallic silver heel patch includes a 'Wings' logo. An exposed-foam nylon tongue and low-cut collar contribute to a DIY look.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Sage Low Triple White (W)
description: The women’s Air Force 1 Sage Low ‘Triple White’ absent of color focuses attention on the construction of the classic silhouette. Here the sneaker is retooled in an all-leather upper with a stitch-and-turn build accented with a tonal Swoosh and heel tab attached by traditional stitching. The upper's pioneering look is enhanced by a revamped platform midsole and supported underneath by an outsole with well-defined teeth.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low SE Tropical Twist
description: The Air Jordan 1 Low SE 'Tropical Twist' gives a new take of the iconic shoe form redesigned in Tropical Twist and Tropical Twist. Its upper spotlights a leather base with overlays and the standard Jordan Wings’ Logo. On the upper a Swoosh branding emphasizes the design with a Nike branded nylon tongue. The midsole is built on top of a rubber outsole with a circular build for traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low Hare Space Jam (GS)
description: The Space Jam x Air Force 1 '07 GS 'Hare' is a grade-school shoe. Dropping for the release of Space Jam: A New Legacy the shoe's leather upper appears in white accented by Light Blue Fury on the tongue tag Swoosh branding and heel patch with the latter two finished in suede. The tongue tags add mismatched Lola and Bugs Bunny designs matched by the quarter panel patches. Underfoot Air in the heel of the midsole provides cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low Computer Chip Space Jam
description: Part of a limited collection for Space Jam: A New Legacy the Space Jam x Air Force 1 '07 'Computer Chip' released in July 2021. Featuring a computer chip-inspired look the shoe's classic basketball construction sports a graphic print throughout built with black leather and black textile with the latter material featured on the contrasting quarter panel. The design itself also sports details that resemble Bugs Bunny and LeBron James' silhouettes and appear in glow-in-the-dark fashion everywhere except for the quarter panel matched underfoot by the concentric rubber outsole that offers traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid Royal (2020)
description: Updating an OG Air Jordan 1 colorway the Air Jordan 1 Mid 'Black Hyper Royal' features more black than its predecessor. The shoe's all-leather upper includes Hyper Royal accents throughout with perforations on the toe box for breathability. The contrasting white midsole provides cushioning via Air.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid Denim Red
description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid 'Denim Red' displays a new take of the iconic shoe design redesigned in Cinnabar and Hemp. Its upper spotlights a leather base with overlays and the standard Wings’ Logo. On the upper a Swoosh emphasizes the design with a nylon contstructed tongue. The Air-sole is built on top of a rubber outsole with a circular build for traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Premium Popcorn
description: Drawing from the iconic movie snack the Air Force 1 '07 Premium 'Popcorn' emerges with a thematic colorway. Built with tumbled leather the shoe's upper appears in Coconut Milk with the heel patch and woven tongue tag sporting Nike branding styled after old-school movie-theater popcorn boxes. The lateral heel includes 'Fresh since 82' while underfoot the white midsole houses Air for cushioning giving way to further Coconut Milk on the concentric rubber outsole.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid Black Siren Red (W)
description: Featuring a classic Jordan Brand colorway the Wmns Air Jordan 1 Mid 'Siren Red' highlights its branding. Built with leather the shoe's upper appears in black highlighted by Siren Red on the tongue collar and Swoosh branding with the color also making its way to the collar. Perforations on the toe box provide breathability while underfoot a white Air midsole provides cushioning and contrast giving way to a black concentric rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Defiant SB LA to Chicago
description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High SB 'LA To Chicago' gives the nod to the rivalry between LA and Chicago which included a Bulls victory over the Lakers in the 1991 NBA Finals. The shoe's leather upper starts out in a Los Angeles mix of Court Purple and University Gold but it's designed to wear away to reveal a black and red colorway reminiscent of the Bulls. The branding includes a Nike SB tag on the tongue while the midsole includes Air for cushioning.

shoeName: adidas Forum Wings 1.0 Low ADV Jeremy Scott Money
description: Using the American designer's currency-inspired print on the textile upper is the Jeremy Scott x adidas Forum Wings 1.0 Low 'Money.' The all-over design which replaces George Washington's likeness with Scott's extends to an ornate 3D wing overlaid on the sneaker's lateral side. Lightweight cushioning arrives via an EVA wedge housed within a durable rubber cupsole. The lateral sidewall had embossed adidas branding with the opposite having Jeremy Scott's signature.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 '07 LX Low Toasty Oil Green
description: Incorporating at least 20% recycled materials by weight and made for winter is the Nike Air Force 1 '07 LX 'Toasty.' Replacing traditional leather the color-blocked upper is made of quilted textile in Brown Kelp Oil Green Sequoia and soft pink hues. Warm white fleece lines the interior and it's built on a solid white rubber cupsole featuring an Air-sole heel unit encapsulated in a lightweight foam wedge.

shoeName: Nike Dunk Low Off-White Lot 1
description: The Off-White x Dunk Low 'Dear Summer - 01 of 50' is the debut colorway of the Dear Summer collection. Built with a mix of canvas and leather the shoe's upper appears in white with silver Swoosh branding highlighting the side wall. Rope laces worked through Flywire cables secure the fit alongside traditional laces while an exposed-foam tongue and pre-yellowed midsole come together to add to the aesthetic. A white plastic zip tie off-center tongue tag and Helvetica text on the medial side add signature Virgil Abloh hits.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low White (2014) (GS)
description: The kids Nike Air Force 1 Low White 2014 (GS) arrives in a classic white on white colorway. The perforations in the upper and along the sides serve to enhance breathability and break up the singular nature of the color palette a bit. Like all Air Force 1 models wearers know and love this design offers modern cushioning for comfort and strong traction thanks to the outsole treads. The kids Nike Air Force 1 Low White 2014 (GS) released in January 2014 and retailed for $75.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High Rookie of the Year
description: In 1985 after starting his career with a remarkable point per game average Michael Jordan won the NBA's Rookie of the Year Award. To celebrate Jordan Brand released the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Rookie of the Year.' The high top features a white-based leather cap with breathability finger box perforations and mudguard knee eyestay and heel overlays of Gold Harvest leather. Hidden on the inside of each upper strap are callouts to the exceptional rookie season of MJ. On the inside of one strap can be discovered ' 1984-85 R.O.Y. 2313 POINTS 28.2 PPG ' and on the other a quote from Jordan.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid SE South Beach
description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE 'South Beach' displays a new iteration of the iconic sneaker design renewed in teal. Its upper spotlights a leather base with overlays and the standard Wings’ Logo. On the upper a Swoosh branding emphasizes the design with a breathable nylon tongue. The Air-sole is built on top of a rubber outsole with a circular build for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT Black Monarch
description: The Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Comfort 'Rookie Of The Year' displays a new iteration of the legendary shoe design updated in Black and White. Its upper accentuates a leather base with overlays and the signature Wings’ Logo. On the upper a Swoosh branding emphasizes the design with a nylon woven tongue. The Air-sole is built on top of a rubber outsole with a circular build for traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Max 1 Anniversary Orange (2020)
description: A vibrant look the Air Max 1 'Magma Orange' features classic color-blocking. Built with a white mesh base the upper is overlaid by grey synthetic suede with a Magma Orange mudguard highlighting the look. The branding and upper eyelets add further Magma Orange while underfoot a visible Max Air unit in the heel of the midsole provides cushioning. A tricolor waffle outsole provides traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low Shattered Backboard
description: The Air Jordan 1 Low 'Shattered Backboard' delivers a chopped down version of the massively popular colorway of the sneaker that started it all. Like its predecessor this low-top edition features a blend of white black and orange on the upper built with leather and nubuck instead of the all-leather construction of the high-top. Branding elements include a Jumpman on the tongue and the Wings logo on the heel.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid Yellow Toe Black
description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE 'Yellow Toe' emerges with a colorful take on the 'Black Toe' concept. The mid-top is built with a leather base overlaid by suede finished in a mix of black and Tour Yellow with white on the quarter panel. Perforations on the toe box provide breathability while underfoot an Air midsole provides cushioning. The outsole sports a pivot-point tread as well as a Tour Yellow finish.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid SE Fearless Maison Chateau Rouge
description: The Maison Chateau Rouge x Air Jordan 1 Mid SE 'Fearless' showcases a unique blend of debossed patterns and materials courtesy of the Parisian lifestyle brand. The sneaker’s distinctive color blocking is highlighted by cinnamon accents on an upper finished in pale blue and vanilla hues. Red hand-stitched detailing on the tongue and heel gives the nod to African-inspired basketry and folk art.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 LV8 Toasty Black White
description: Delivering a winterized version of the sneaker icon in a sustainable build with at least 20% recycled materials is the Nike Air Force 1 '07 LV8 'Toasty.' The upper is made with black quilted textile with tonal synthetic suede overlays a contrasting white Swoosh and a fleece-lined interior for cozy comfort. Nike's pinwheel logo is on the woven tongue tag with a blue Swoosh embroidered on the heel tab. It's built on a white rubber midsole and a speckled outsole made in part with Nike Grind composed of recycled scraps from the manufacturing process.

shoeName: Nike Air Max 1 Chinese New Year Longevity (2020)
description: Releasing in Jaunary 2020 the Air Max 1 Premium EP 'CNY - Longevity' features a bold festive design. The shoe's upper includes an acid-washed denim toe box with the collar and heel sporting butterfly and floral motifs. Metallic gold accents the eyelets and the leather quarter panel includes a dragon design. The patent leather mudguard incorporates embossed Chinese characters while underfoot visible Air in the heel of the midsole provides cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Max 1 Anniversary Red (2017/2018 Restock Pair)
description: The 2017 reissue of the Air Max 1 OG brings back the inaugural colorway of the running shoe that introduced visible Air cushioning to the masses. This 30th anniversary build is faithful to the original utilizing a white mesh base with synthetic suede overlays in grey and contrasting pops of red on the Swoosh and mudguard.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid White Black Cyber Pink
description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE 'Cyber Active Fuchsia' emerges with a key element borrowed from the Air Jordan 11. Namely the shoe's white leather upper is overlaid by patent leather in black. The Swoosh also sports patent leather finished in a mismatched mix of Cyber and blue while Active Fuchsia marks the collar and heel made with further patent leather. Underfoot the Air midsole gives way to a concentric rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: adidas Ultra Boost 1.0 Core White
description: At the annual Powerhouse concert for LA radio station Power 106 two weeks before their official release date in June 2015 Kanye West famously revealed these sneakers. The shoes sold out in pre-orders instantly. This is one of the cleanest and most coveted Ultra Boost colors ever released dressed in all white except for the black outsole and metallic Ultra Boost lettering on the heel cup.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low Wheat Dark Mocha
description: Originally released in 2001 exclusively in Japan the Air Force 1 Low 'Wheat Mocha' emerges with the same look. The shoe's upper is built with nubuck finished in Wheat and complemented by Dark Mocha on the inner lining and tongue tag. Underfoot a semitranslucent gum rubber midsole houses Air in the heel to provide cushioning giving way to a Dark Mocha rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Max 1 Anniversary Green (2020)
description: Sporting OG-inspired color-blocking the Air Max 1 'Hunter Green' released in July 2020. Built with a white mesh base the upper is overlaid by grey synthetic suede with green on the mudguard and branding. Underfoot the midsole houses visible Air in the heel for cushioning giving way to a waffle rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low Swarovski Retroreflective Crystals Black (W)
description: Giving a luxe makeover to the classic shoe is the Swarovski x Nike women's Air Force 1 LXX 'Black.' A modular four-piece shroud is secured with functional screws and studded with 228 Swarovski crystals on the black leather upper. Each piece is made exclusively for Nike and features an unfaceted retroreflective finish. It's mounted on a matching black rubber cupsole with an Air-sole heel unit and a pivot-pint rubber outsole. A screwdriver is included to be able to customize.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid Banned (2020) (PS)
description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid PS 'Banned' is a preschool iteration of the iconic Jordan Brand colorway. The shoe's upper is built with leather appearing in a classic mix of black and University Red with added University Red on the eyestay. Unlike its full-size counterpart a heel pull-loop is included to provide easy on and off while the usual perforations on the toe box provide breathability. Underfoot a white rubber midsole gives way to a concentric University Red rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid Milan
description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid 'Milan' released as part of the three-shoe City Pack. Inspired by the Italy's fashion capital the shoe's pastel colorway is drawn from the city's gothic architecture. The overlays sport varying textures while a leather MLN hang-tag completes the thematic look. The classic tooling includes Air in the heel of the midsole.

shoeName: Nike Air Max 1 Parra (2018)
description: After decades of collaborations between Amsterdam-based artist Piet Parra and Nike this July 2018 release celebrates Parra and Nike's reunion on yet another Air Max 1. With a track jacket and Zoom Spiridon the shoe features bright and colourful pieces from the artist inspired by the landscape in the Netherlands and his love of visual pop culture.

shoeName: Jordan 1 High FlyEase Turf Orange
description: The Air Jordan 1 High FlyEase 'Turf Orange' displays a new iteration of the legendary shoe design redesigned in Black and Turf Orange. Its upper spotlights a leather base with overlays and the standard Wings’ Logo. On the upper a Swoosh emphasizes the design with a nylon contstructed tongue. The midsole is built on top of a rubber outsole with a circular build for traction.

shoeName: adidas Ultra Boost 1.0 Burgundy
description: The adidas Ultra Boost 1.0 appears in its sock-like Primeknit construction with a burgundy colorway. On the tongue branding faded orange accents are present while the white midsole Boost provides a smooth ride. An extra orange hit appears in the underfoot torsion bar.

shoeName: Nike Air Max 1 Tokyo Maze
description: Released as part of the Nike: On Air contest that gave people a chance to give people to create their on Air Max models the Air Max 1 'On Air: Tokyo Maze' was designed by Tokyo's Yuta Takuman. The shoe's black and white labyrinthine upper and vibrant laces are modeled after the city's subway system. Underfoot a solid black midsole houses a red Max Air unit in the heel which pays tribute to the Tokyo Tower.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low SB UNC
description: Nike tapped Eric Koston to create the Eric Koston x Air Jordan 1 Low SB 'Powder Blue' updating the iconic silhouette that Koston midssed out on as a kid. The low-top emerges with a white leather upper overlaid by Dark Powder Blue on the toe eyestay Swoosh and heel. A classic 'Wings' logo emerges on the heel while the inside of the tongue sports Koston's signature. Air cushioning and a concentric outsole support the fit underfoot.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro Chicago (2015)
description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Chicago' 2015 colorway features full-leather uppers in Bulls team colors. The 'Chicago' was first retroed in 1994 and stayed true to the 1985 design. Further retros were released in 2013 with small changes to the design and again in 2015 with the original branding details: the Nike Air logo on the tongue and the original clean heel without the Jumpman logo.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro Top 3
description: Nike merged three original Air Jordan 1 colorways (Bred Chicago and Royal ) into a fresh colorway in 2016 known as the 'Top 3'. With the Wings logo on the ankle and the Nike Air branding on the insole and tongue the sneaker comes in mismatched' color panels and outsoles while remaining true to the original design. 'Top 3' also refers to Jordan being drafted third overall in the NBA draft.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 LX Reveal Black Swoosh (W)
description: The Wmns Air Force 1 Low LX 'Tear Away' emerges with a wear-away design. As a result the toe box sports 'Tear Here' and removing the top layer reveals a series of vibrant hues. The Swoosh also sports a design that plays to the theme while underfoot Air in the midsole provides cushioning. The shoe released in packaging with instructions.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro Black Toe (2016)
description: One of the initial Air Jordan 1 line colorways the 'Black Toe' Air Jordan 1 Retro grew in popularity after being featured in several Nike promotional campaigns (including the picture inspired by the Jordan logo itself). Surprisingly however Jordan only wore this colorway in a couple of games improving its popularity.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 React White Light Bone
description: The Air Force 1 React QS 'White Ice' brings a neutral look to its hybrid construction. Built with textile the upper is highlighted by reflective detailing throughout while an exaggerated eyestay adds to the aesthetic. Underfoot a drop-in React footbed works with Air in the midsole to provide cushioning giving way to a Rush Coral outsole for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High Not for Resale Varsity Red
description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG NRG ‘Not For Resale’ features bold messages printed across the upper and midsole. They include ‘No Photos’ embroidered across the heel of the left and right shoe ‘Wear Me’ across the tongues and ‘Please Crease’ stamped on each toe box. The printed phrases are used to enhance classic color blocking that stands out against a white leather base with contrasting black overlays and a burst of Varsity Red around the collar.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low Shadow Triple Black (W)
description: The women’s Air Force 1 Shadow 'Triple Black' dropped in 2019 as part of a new wave AF1 models intended to shift the design paradigm of the classic Nike silhouette from a female perspective. This pair features an all-black layered upper that features doubled-up detailing on the Swoosh eyestay heel tab and mudguard. A slightly heightened foam midsole is supported by a cored-out rubber outsole.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 React White Black Red
description: Part of Nike's D/MS/X line the Air Force 1 React 'D/MS/X' is a hybrid take on the basketball classic. The shoe's leather upper includes a mesh quarter panel with an oversized Swoosh contrasting the side wall. A wavy eyestay adds to the aesthetic while perforations on the toe box provide breathability. Underfoot the midsole incorporates drop-in React foam in place of the usual Max Air with Ramp Air in the heel.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro Shattered Backboard
description: By throwing down a monstrous dunk while wearing an orange black and white uniform Michael Jordan broke a backboard during a Nike Europe tour in 1985. A 2015 Air Jordan 1 'Shattered Backboard' was released to commemorate the moment and uniform. This sneaker maintains the branding of black laces and Nike but swaps the orange toe box and black around the white toe and tongue.

shoeName: adidas Ultra Boost DNA 1.0 Aqua ZX 8000
description: Drawing from the 1988 runner the UltraBoost 1.0 DNA 'ZX 8000' emerges with an OG-style colorway. Featuring a 2015 UltraBoost-style Primeknit upper the vibrant look includes a Three-Stripes lacing cage for support with an external heel counter offering stability. Suede overlays the forefoot to add to the ZX 8000 aesthetic while underfoot tonal full-length Boost provides cushioning working with a Torsion bar for stability and a Continental rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Foamposite One Light Smoke Grey (GS)
description: A kids'-exclusive look the Little Posite One GS 'Rainbow Pixel' features a subtly vibrant look. The shoe's signature Foamposite upper includes an iridescent sheen throughout complemented by grey nubuck trim on the collar and eyestay. Underfoot the midfoot shank sports a rainbow graident to bring further color to the design.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 LV8 Sashiko (W)
description: Inspired by traditional Japanese embroidery the Wmns Air Force 1 Low '07 LV8 'Sashiko' emerges with a patchwork-style upper in place of the usual leather build. The classic basketball silhouette includes a paneled construction on the upper incorporating a navy woven checkboard pattern white and black knit and white suede on the eyestay heel patch and Swoosh branding. The heel patch and lace deubré add gold Japanese characters to the look with further characters visible through the translucent rubber outsole underfoot.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High Satin Shattered Backboard (W)
description: Before Michael Jordan’s exploits made him an all-time NBA great he famously shattered a backboard during a 1985 exhibition game in Italy. Nike went on to commemorate the moment with the ‘Shattered Backboard’ colorway. The Wmns Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Satin Shattered Backboard’ brings that look to a women’s exclusive shoe. Constructed with full-grain leather and low-shine satin the upper is finished in a mix of black Starfish and Sail that recreates the look of the uniform Jordan wore during that game. The lining also features black Satin while the rubber outsole is finished in Starfish.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low LXX Toasty (W)
description: Showcasing a fall palette on an updated build made for colder weather is the Nike women's Air Force 1 '07 Low LXX 'Toasty.' Lined in warm fleece the paneled upper is made from quilted textile in brown tan and orange hues. A black synthetic suede Swoosh is featured with a woven tongue tag marked with Nike's pinwheel logo symbolizing the shoe's made of at least 20% recycled materials by weight. On the bottom of the low-top is a white rubber cupsole with Nike Air cushioning encapsulated in a foam wedge.

shoeName: On The Roger Pro Kith White Ivory Black
description: DISCLAIMER: There is manufacturer variance in this product. Not all pairs include the small red flag on the lateral side of shoe.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid SE Fearless Melody Ehsani (W)
description: The Melody Ehsani x women’s Air Jordan 1 Mid 'Fearless' is a collaborative release that showcases the signature style of the Los Angeles-based designer. In addition to mismatched coloring between the left and right shoe the sneaker features a large gold watch dubrae and a hand lettered quote on the midsole that reads 'If you knew what you had was rare you would never waste it.'

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid Signal Blue (TD)
description: A toddlers' shoe the Air Jordan 1 Mid SE TD 'Signal Blue' features a University of North Carolina-style colorway. The shoe's upper is built with a white leather base overlaid by Signal Blue patent leather matched by the stitching on the Swoosh. Black contrast emerges throughout while a heel pull-loop has been added for easy on and off. Underfoot a white foam midsole provides cushioning with a black rubber outsole included for traction.
